# White-Label Reseller & Deployment Guide

## Overview
This platform is designed to be easily rebranded and deployed for multiple tenants. This guide explains how to configure branding, set up the environment, and deploy the application.

## 1. Prerequisites
- **Node.js**: v18 or higher
- **Firebase Project**: A new project created in the [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com/)
- **PackageManager**: `npm` or `pnpm`

## 2. Environment Setup
The application relies on environment variables for its core identity.

1.  **Duplicate Template**: Copy [.env.template](file:///c:/Users/user/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/White_label/.env.template) to `.env.local` (for local dev) or set these variables in your deployment platform (Vercel/Netlify).
2.  **Required Variables**:

| Variable | Description | Example |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_BRAND_NAME` | The visible name of the store | "My Awesome Shop" |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_BRAND_TAGLINE` | Tagline appearing in Hero/Meta | "Quality goods for you" |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_BRAND_LOGO` | Path to logo (relative or absolute URL) | "/images/my-logo.png" |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_BRAND_FAVICON`| Path to favicon | "/favicon.ico" |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY` | Firebase Config | (From Firebase Console) |

> [!TIP]
> **Pro Tip**: You do NOT need to touch the code to change the brand name. Just update `NEXT_PUBLIC_BRAND_NAME` and redeploy!

## 3. Configuration Management
The platform uses a "Tiered Configuration" system:
1.  **Firestore (Highest Priority)**: Settings stored in the `/config/site` document in Firestore override everything. Use the Admin Panel to change these on the fly without redeploying.
2.  **Environment Variables (Medium Priority)**: Used if no Firestore config exists (or for static generation).
3.  **Defaults (Lowest Priority)**: Generic "White Label Store" values hardcoded in [src/types/site-config.ts](file:///c:/Users/user/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/White_label/src/types/site-config.ts).

### Changing Defaults in Code
If you want to change the *hardcoded fallback* (e.g., if you are reselling this as a specific base product), edit:
- **File**: [src/types/site-config.ts](file:///c:/Users/user/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/White_label/src/types/site-config.ts)
- **Object**: `DEFAULT_SITE_CONFIG`

## 4. Assets & Styling
- **Logos**: Place default images in `/public`. Update `NEXT_PUBLIC_BRAND_LOGO` to point to them.
- **Colors**: The theme is controlled via Tailwind + CSS variables.
    - Edit `src/app/globals.css` to change the root color variables (`--brand-primary`, `--brand-secondary`, etc.) for a completely new color scheme.

## 5. Deployment Steps (Vercel Example)
1.  **Import Project**: Connect your Git repository to Vercel.
2.  **Environment Config**: Copy the contents of your filled-out `.env.local` into Vercel's "Environment Variables" section.
3.  **Deploy**: Click Deploy.
4.  **Post-Deploy**:
    - Go to your specific Firebase Console -> Firestore.
    - Create a collection `config` and document `site` (optional, for dynamic overrides).
    - **Security**: Deploy the security rules using `firebase deploy --only firestore:rules,storage:rules`.

## 6. Accessing Admin Panel
- Navigate to `/admin`
- The implemented middleware (if active) and `AdminPROTECTOR` will require you to log in.
- Ensure your user account has `role: 'admin'` in the `users` Firestore collection to access write features.
